com.novartis.opensource.yada

Class YADARequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.novartis.opensource.yada.YADARequest

  • public class YADARequest
extends Object
    A utility class for marshalling url params into instance variables, and serving as a portable structure for passing parameter values across layers of the API. This class also sets default YADA parameter values, converts values into appropriate object types, or nestles values in data structures.
    Since:
    0.1.0.0
    Author:
    David Varon

      • getCount

        public boolean getCount()
        Standard accessor for variable. If true, and the query protocol is Parser.JDBC, the core code is wrapped in a SELECT COUNT(*) query, which is added to the request in the processing phase, to return the total result count of the query. This is particularly useful when executing the query from a GUI client which uses pagination. IF set to false, only the original query is executed. For more details see the Users' Guide If the query protocol is Parser.REST or Parser.SOAP, count is automatically set to false.
        Returns:
        boolean value of count

      • getCountOnly

        public boolean getCountOnly()
        Standard accessor for variable. If true, and the query protocol is Parser.JDBC, the core code is wrapped in a SELECT COUNT(*) query, and only this query is executed in the processing phase. Only the record count is returned. No data is returned. If the query protocol is Parser.REST or Parser.SOAP, countOnly is ignored. For more details see the Users' Guide
        Returns:
        boolean value of countOnly
